1. Recipe App - ( React P2 )
React

FrontEnd

Description:

A dynamic recipe app that fetches data from a public meals API, allowing users to search and filter recipes based on ingredients, categories, or meal types.

Project Documentation:
Recipe App
Develop a dynamic recipe application that allows users to browse, search, and filter
recipes based on various criteria using data fetched from a public meals API. This
project focuses on implementing core React functionalities, ensuring a responsive
user interface, and providing a smooth user experience.
What to do?
Recipe Listings:
● Provide a clean UI to list recipes fetched from a public meals API.
● Display key recipe details such as name, thumbnail image, and category.
● Each recipe card should be clickable to view complete recipe details on a
separate page or modal.
Search and Filter:
● Implement a search bar to allow users to search for recipes by name or
keyword.
● Add filter options for users to narrow down recipes by ingredients, categories,
or meal types.
● Ensure filters and search can work together for refined results.
Recipe Details:
● Show full recipe information including instructions, ingredients, category, and
video link (if available).
● Allow users to return to the main recipe list easily.

Favorites (Optional):
● Allow users to mark recipes as favorites.
● Store favorites in localStorage so they persist across sessions.
User Features:
● View a list of recipes and search through them.
● Filter recipes by categories and ingredients.
● View full details for a selected recipe.
● (Optional) Save favorite recipes for later viewing.
Techstacks needs to be used:
● React JS
● TailwindCSS for styling
● Axios or fetch API for making requests
● Public API: https://www.themealdb.com/api.php
How do I submit my work?
● Deploy your web application using Netlify (https://www.netlify.com)
● Push all your work files to GitHub.
● Submit your URLs in the portal.
